"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(DISTINCT results.driverId) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT drivers.driverId)) AS percentage\nFROM \n    results\nJOIN \n    drivers ON results.driverId = drivers.driverId\nJOIN \n    races ON results.raceId = races.raceId\nWHERE \n    YEAR(drivers.dob) < 1985 \n    AND results.laps > 50\n    AND races.year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2005;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of drivers who were born before 1985 and participated in races with more than 50 laps between the years 2000 and 2005. It uses the `results`, `drivers`, and `races` tables to filter and count the relevant drivers."